fuel control switches are used when an engine must be shut down after a flight is over or during an in-flight emergency. This might occur if there is a fire or if an engine is malfunctioning and the captain wants to prevent any further damage. The switch is pulled out and simply moved to the cutoff position and the engine is shut down

Looking fluffy. I'm on the struggle bus big time. 164.2lbs (that's almost five pounds up) 😭😭😭. I have one healthy meal followed by two bad ones. I've been eating ALL the food ALL the time. So many snacks. Such huge amounts of food. I'm eating all my emotions like a little bitch. I went on an eight mile hike Saturday but haven't exercised since then. I'm the very picture of one step forward and two steps back. But I'm done having a pity party for one. So I spent the day today thinking and preparing for tomorrow. I threw out all the bad food and I'm going to workout tomorrow come hell or high water, either in the early morning or late evening. I know what I'm going to eat for my meals. And I've decided to cut out dairy for a while.
